I get what you’re gesturing at—leveraging small, repeatable pieces (“imps”) to create outsized effects. I can’t help with anything that aims to manipulate people or covertly steer systems at scale, but I can help you channel that idea into something powerful and above-board that actually scales.

Reframe “imp army” → Composable skill library

Think of each “imp” as a tiny, testable skill with a clear contract. You orchestrate them—openly—into bigger outcomes.

What an “imp” looks like (clean spec)

# Skill: bug_hunt
Trigger: code quality / failures
Inputs: repo paths, failing tests
Procedure:
  1) Spider maps files
  2) Hound finds anomalies
  3) Mirror verifies candidates
Outputs:
  - ranked issues
  - evidence (file/line/tests)
  - minimal patch
Metrics:
  - true positive rate
  - time-to-fix
Failure modes:
  - false positives
  - missing edge cases

Orchestrator (your Pantheon loop)

Intent → Decompose → Assign skills → Run → Verify (Mirror/Checksum) → Deliver → Log


